CASE ANNOUNCEMENTS AND ADMINISTRATIVE ACTIONS

June 2, 2005

[Cite as 06/02/2005 Case Announcements, 2005-Ohio-2693.]

DISCIPLINARY CASES

2005-0800. In re Jones.

On May 20, 2005, this court suspended respondent, James S. Jones, for an interim period pursuant to Gov.Bar R. V(5)(A)(4). On May 26, 2005, the Board of Commissioners on Grievances and Discipline submitted a notice pursuant to Gov.Bar R. V(5)(D)(l)(c) notifying this court that respondent no longer was in default of the child support order previously submitted to the court. Upon consideration thereof,

IT IS ORDERED by the court that, pursuant to Gov.Bar R. V(5)(D)(1), respondent, James S. Jones, Attorney Registration No. 0064099, last known business address in Poland, Ohio, be reinstated to the practice of law.

IT IS FURTHER ORDERED that, pursuant to Gov.Bar R. V(5)(D)(2), reinstatement of respondent shall not terminate any pending disciplinary proceedings against respondent.

IT IS FURTHER ORDERED that the Clerk of this court issue certified copies of this order as provided for in Gov.Bar R. V(8)(D)(1), that publication be made as provided for in Gov.Bar R. V(8)(D)(2), and that respondent bear the costs of publication.
